usage:
    slc --version
    slc run [--platform <target>] [--cache-dir <dir>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    slc fmt [--check] [<file-or-dir> ...]
    slc compile [--platform <target>] [--cache-dir <dir>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [-o <output>]
    slc genpkg[:backend] [--platform <target>] [--cache-dir <dir>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [out]
    slc check <srcfile>
    slc checkpkg [--platform <target>] [--cache-dir <dir>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    slc lex <srcfile>
    slc ast <srcfile>
    slc mir [--platform <target>] [--cache-dir <dir>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    slc --version
    slc --help

<target> is one of: cli-libc (default), cli-eval, wasm-min, playbit
`slc run` defaults to cli-eval when --platform is omitted
